    "created_at": "2026-03-31T00:00:00Z",
    "notes": [
      "struct.pack() and struct.unpack() convert between Python values and C struct layout in binary form.",
      "Format string prefixes: '>' = big-endian (most significant byte first), '<' = little-endian, '!' = network byte order (= big-endian, RFC 1700), '=' = native byte order without alignment, '@' = native byte order with alignment. This spec uses '>' and '<' and '!' exclusively.",
      "Format characters used in this spec: B=uint8, b=int8, H=uint16, h=int16, I=uint32, i=int32, Q=uint64, q=int64, f=float32, d=float64.",
      "struct.error is raised for mismatched buffer sizes and invalid format strings. It is a subclass of Exception (not ValueError).",
      "calcsize(fmt) returns the number of bytes struct.pack(fmt, ...) would produce."
    ]
  },

